# Git commit & push attribution

This repo must never publish AI or foreign git identities.

## Required local identity

Always use this repo-local author only:

- `user.name` = `AtiqurCode`
- `user.email` = `atqur9@gmail.com`

Before any commit or push, verify:

```sh
git config --local --get user.name
git config --local --get user.email
```

If missing or wrong, set them locally (never rely on global):

```sh
git config --local user.name "AtiqurCode"
git config --local user.email "atqur9@gmail.com"
```

## Hard bans

Do **not** create, amend, or push commits that include any of the following as author, committer, co-author, trailer, or message signature:

- Claude / Anthropic
- Cursor / CursorAgent / cursoragent
- Any other global git user (for example `Atiqur <atiqur@itconquest.com>`)
- `Co-authored-by` trailers for AI tools
- Commit messages that advertise an AI assistant as helper/author

## Commit message rules

- Keep messages human and project-focused
- No phrases like "Generated with Claude", "via Cursor", "Cursor Agent", etc.
- No AI model names in commit bodies or trailers

## Push checklist

Before `git push`:

1. Confirm branch is the intended one (`master` for this repo)
2. Confirm latest commit author is `AtiqurCode <atqur9@gmail.com>`
3. Reject/fix the commit if author/committer is anything else
